{"title_page": "Pagodite", "text_new": "{{refimprove|date=May 2015}}\n[[File:Pagodite for sale 20070726 155540 NEC 0014.jpg|thumb|Pagodite for sale in Japan]]\n'''Pagodite''' is the name of a stone used by [[China|Chinese]] artisans for carving [[pagoda]]s and similar objects.   Usually soft and sometimes soapy, it can be a greyish green or greyish yellow colour. Names also used in this context are agalmatolite,<ref name=\"Manutchehr-Danai2013\">{{cite book\n|author=Mohsen Manutchehr-Danai|title=Dictionary of Gems and Gemology|date=9 March 2013|publisher=Springer Science & Business Media|isbn=978-3-662-04288-5|page=351}} [https://books.google.com/books?id=2UX1CAAAQBAJ&pg=PA351 Excerpts available] at [[Google Books]].</ref> [[steatite]], [[pyrophyllite]] and [[pinite]]; sometimes also referred to (loosely) as [[soapstone]].<ref name=\"Dennys2012\">{{cite book\n|author=Nicholas Belfield Dennys|title=The Treaty Ports of China and Japan: A Complete Guide to the Open Ports of Those Countries, Together with Peking, Yedo, Hongkong and Macao|date=2012|orig-year=first published 1867|publisher=Cambridge University Press|isbn=978-1-108-04590-2|pages=278}} [https://books.google.com/books?id=NpyNH0UrKvUC&pg=PA278  Excerpts available] at [[Google Books]].</ref> Small pagodite pieces are used as traditional writing tools in Japan.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Sculpture materials]]\n\n\n{{sculpture-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{refimprove|date=May 2015}}\n'''Pagodite''' is the name of a stone used by [[China|Chinese]] artisans for carving [[pagoda]]s and similar objects.   Usually soft and sometimes soapy, it can be a greyish green or greyish yellow colour. Names also used in this context are agalmatolite,<ref name=\"Manutchehr-Danai2013\">{{cite book\n|author=Mohsen Manutchehr-Danai|title=Dictionary of Gems and Gemology|date=9 March 2013|publisher=Springer Science & Business Media|isbn=978-3-662-04288-5|page=351}} [https://books.google.com/book